  "text": "The path-signature feature, pioneered by Chen [CITATION_1] in the form of iterated integrals, can extract a sufficient quantity of information contained in a finite path (e.g., in online handwriting) to solve any linear differential equation. The path-signature feature was first introduced for the recognition of online handwritten characters by Graham [CITATION_2] . In this paper, we discovered a method for extracting sufficient writer information from handwriting using the path-signature feature.",
